hooks/scope-guard.py line 247-250 _HEREDOC_RE: r'<<[- ]*[quote]?([A-Za-z_]\w*)[quote]?[^
]*
(.*
)*?\1
?'. The 'closing \1' requires the delimiter to start at column 0 (no leading whitespace). But the <<- form of bash heredocs strips leading TABS from both body lines AND the close delimiter, so the closing line can be tab-indented. The regex won't match the close, leaving the heredoc body exposed to write-pattern detection — yielding a false-positive DENY on any > or > inside an indented heredoc. Update the regex to allow leading whitespace on the closing line (e.g., r'\s*\1') when '<<-' was specified.
